Coordinating Committee of Korean Friends Formed in Britain 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of the Coordinating Committee of Korean Friends was held in London on Dec. 6.
 Present there were Harpal Brar, chairman of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Great Britain "Marxist-Leninist", its International Secretary Ella Rule, Andy Brooks, general secretary of the Central Committee of the New Communist Party of Britain, a member of the Central Committee of the Revolutionary Communist Party of Britain "Marxist-Leninist", Keith Bennet, secretary general of the European Society for the Study of the Juche Idea, and Dermot Hudson, chairman of the British Association for the Study of Songun Policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials of the DPRK embassy in London were present there on invitation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ceremony elected the chairman of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Great Britain "Marxist-Leninist" chairman of the coordinating committee and the chairman of the British Association for the Study of Songun Policy its vice-chairman and the member of the Central Committee of the Revolutionary Communist Party of Britain "Marxist-Leninist" its secretary general. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ceremony adopted the statute of the committee and decided to elect its leadership once every year.

More Stock-breeding Farms Built 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- A lot of stock-breeding bases have been  built or reconstructed on an expansion basis in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea this year,the 60th birthday of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Servicepersons constructed Duck Farm No.115 in a stony area in a little over one  year. It, with a total floor space of more than 50,000 square meters, is equipped with modern facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Working people of South Hamgyong Province automatized and computerized all the production processes of the Kwangpho Duck Farm and put the production structures on a scientific and technical basis, thus converting it into a poultry production base with a production capacity of thousands of tons.
 Korean Working people  reconstructed the Pukchang Duck Farm and Kusong Chicken Farm on a modern line and completed the third stage of expansion project of the Kyenam Stock-breeding Farm with a firm resolve to build a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first stage projects for modernization of the Kanggye and Sinuiju Duck Farms were carried out successfully and a number of other stock-breeding centers reconstructed or built to meet the demand of the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a result, the stock-breeding of the country has been put on more solid material and technical level based on latest science and technology.

Juche 94 Adorned with Infinite Devotion and Great Leadership 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has continued field guidance from the beginning of the year.
 He visited a number of industrial establishments and units of the Korean People's Army across the country from a machine building plant in the northwestern area of the country to a KPA Unit on the front in the south and from a saltern on the east coast to a ship repair factory on the west coast.
 Kim Jong Il provided on-the-spot guidance to units and sub-units of the KPA including a women's company once every three days in April and various months and to many units once every two days in some months including November when he visited Duck Farm No.115 built by servicepersons and factories in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His field guidance includes all sectors of the national economy for building a great prosperous powerful nation. Among them are Ryongsong Machine Complex, Miru Plain in North Hwanghae Province, Hungnam Fertilizer Complex, Taean Friendship Glass Factory, Pyongyang 326 Electric Wire Factory, gravity-fed waterway, a saltern, construction sites, a pharmaceutical factory and a theatre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During working tour, he met with a lot of people from all walks of life to  converse with them and showed warm care of their living conditions.
 While inspecting units of the KPA, he saw trainings of servicepersons and looked round educational rooms, bedrooms, mess halls, kitchens, wash-cum-bath houses, non-staple food stores, tunnel cool stores, laundries and other cultural and welfare facilities to acquaint himself with military service and life of soldiers and bestow fatherly love on them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At industrial establishments and construction sites, he indicated ways for application of latest scientific and technical successes that even scientists and technicians did not conceive and ways to bring earlier the completion of projects while ensuring the highest quality of structures to suit the requirement of the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He continued his indefatigable inspection tour even on sultry, rainy and snowy days throughout the year.
 It was the midsummer days when he visited some units and sub-units of the KPA along the front line and the newly built Wonsan Bay Saltern.
 He did not stop his field guidance even in January, the coldest month of the year, and in December during which coldest weather ever since 1910 continued for over 20 days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Finding himself among the people all the year round, he has closely rallied the whole Party, whole army and the entire people as Songun revolutionary comrades with his brilliant leadership ability, lofty moral virtues, and outstanding political ability and aroused them in the general march of Songun revolution. Juche 94 (2005) is shining with brilliant revolutionary activities of    Kim Jong Il, a political veteran.

Many Industrial Fine Art Works Created 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- A lot of the industrial fine art works have been created in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Choe Chi Ho, a section chief of the State Quality Control Bureau, told KCNA that more than 1,200 designs drawn by art studios, educational institutions and industrial establishments including the Industrial Fine Art Studio under the Ministry of Machine-Building Industries, Light Industrial Fine Art Studio under the Ministry of Light Industry, Mansudae Art Studio, Pyongyang University of Fine Arts and Pyongyang Cosmetic Factory were examined and registered this year. Over 500 pieces out of them have already been applied to production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the designs are new and rich in their content and form. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The Industrial Fine Art Studio under the Ministry of Machine-Building Industries advanced designs for "Huichon" A-type digital universal lathe and various kinds of machines, "June 15" electric locomotive, "Puhung" tram-car, "Rakwon" hydraulic excavator and "Phungnyon" combine. Their form and color are peculiar and varied. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Light Industrial Fine Art Studio under the Ministry of Light Industry produced designs for silk cloth and quilt cover gracefully decorated with different patterns and colors, designs for various kinds of vessel decorations and designs for many foodstuff trademarks.
 More than 60 brand designs for processed potato including potato starch noodle, frozen-potato noodle and fermented-potato vinegar have been introduced into production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Mansudae Art Studio and Pyongyang University of Fine Arts have also produced designs for the exterior and interior of Pyongyang Conservatory, the reconstruction of the East Pyongyang Grand Theater, monument to the Youth Hero Motor-way, theaters and cultural halls and for various kinds of parks, fountains, fences and street decoration. They were all created to suit the modern aesthetics.

GNP's Traitorous "Human Rights" Racket under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- The "human rights" racket kicked up by the south Korean ultra-right conservative forces including the "Grand National Party" against the north is an unpardonable treacherous criminal act to incite antagonism and confrontation between the south and the north and do harm to the fellow countrymen in the north according to the U.S. script to isolate and stifle it. Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed commentary.
 The commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S. forces of south Korea including the GNP kicked up a row over the non-existent "human rights issue" in the north at the instigation of the U.S. Not content with this, they have become desperate in their smear campaign by staging what they called "international conference." It is really deplorable and ridiculous for them to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits a more serious attention is that their "human rights" racket is timed to coincide with the U.S. recent frantic "human rights" offensive against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is disgusting and resentful for these forces to dance to the tune of foreign forces, not knowing what human rights are like, bereft of the consciousness of being Koreans and sensitivity to the times. This despicable action can be taken only by the group of traitors who seek a way out in slandering and doing harm to fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are completely steeped in the American-style view on the value of "human rights," while serving the U.S., having neither proper opinion nor political principle. It is imprudent and ridiculous for these elements to dare impose this view on the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no need to argue that the "human rights" offensive launched by them with the backing of the U.S. is aimed at "overthrowing the system" in the north. But they are seriously mistaken. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean ultra-right conservative forces had better cool their heads overheated with their "human rights" racket against the north and behave prudently.

Rodong Sinmun on Establishing Juche in Ideological Work 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today dedicates a signed article to the 50th anniversary of the publication of President Kim Il Sung's famous work "On Eliminating Dogmatism and Formalism and Establishing Juche in Ideological Work". 
 Clarified in the work are the principled issues to be held fast to with all consistency by the working-class party in deepening its ideological work and leading the revolution and construction ranging from the necessity for thoroughly eliminating flunkeyism and dogmatism and establishing Juche to the ways of doing so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the course of applying the ideas, theories and policies laid down in the work the Korean people have maintained the viewpoint and stand of thinking and practicing everything, placing the Korean revolution above anything else, and settling all the issues by their wisdom and efforts, fully aware that they are the master of the revolution and construction. The work is an immortal one of historic significance in firmly preserving the tradition of the Korean revolution and achieving its victorious advance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung's idea on eliminating dogmatism and formalism and strictly establishing Juche in the ideological work has been successfully carried forward and its validity and vitality are being fully proved day by day under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Establishing Juche in the ideological work under socialism presents itself as a very important issue related to the cause of socialism and the destiny of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has led the cause of the Korean revolution to a proud victory by successfully carrying forward and developing in depth the tradition of establishing Juche provided by Kim Il Sung and exploits performed by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle to establish Juche has reached a new stage in the Songun era when the great Songun idea is being applied to all fields. It is thanks to this idea that the Korean people have been the great people having high national pride and strong revolutionary confidence generation after generation.
